a]]\n| [[Wide Receiver]]\n| 1 year / $5 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001102752/article/lions-resign-wr-danny-amendola-for-1year-deal |title=Lions re-sign WR Danny Amendola for 1-year deal |website=NFL.com |first=Adam |last=Maya |date=February 22, 2020 |accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 14\n| [[Don Muhlbach]]\n| [[Long Snapper]]\n|1 year / $1.135 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-re-sign-ls-don-muhlbach-x3928 |title=Lions re-sign LS Don Muhlbach |work=Detroit Lions |date=March 14, 2020 |accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 21\n| [[Miles Killebrew]]\n| [[Linebacker]]\n| 1 year / $2 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-agree-to-terms-with-safety-miles-killebrew |title=Lions agree to terms with safety Miles Killebrew |work=Detroit Lions |date=March 20, 2020 |accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 24\n| [[Oday Aboushi]] \n| [[Guard (gridiron football)|Guard]]\n| 1 year / $1.1875  million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-agree-to-terms-with-ol-oday-aboushi |title=Lions agree to terms with OL Oday Aboushi |work=Detroit Lions |date=March 24, 2020 |accessdate=March 24, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 14\n| [[Kenny Wiggins]] \n| [[Guard (gridiron football)|Guard]]\n| 1 year / \u2013 \n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-agree-to-terms-with-ol-kenny-wiggins |title=Lions agree to terms with OL Kenny Wiggins |work=Detroit Lions |date=April 14, 2020 |accessdate=April 14, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Trades===\n*On March 18, the Lions acquired [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] [[Duron Harmon]] and a seventh-round pick from the [[New England Patriots]] in exchange for a fifth-round pick in the [[2020 NFL Draft]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-acquire-s-duron-harmon-via-trade-with-new-england-patriots |title=Lions acquire S Duron Harmon via trade with New 