=\n* {{official website|http://www.detroitlions.com}}\n\n{{Detroit Lions}}\n{{Detroit Lions seasons}}\n{{2020 NFL season by team}}\n\n[[Category:2020 National Football League season by team|Detroit]]\n[[Category:Detroit Lions seasons]]\n[[Category:2020 in sports in Michigan|Detroit Lions]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Detroit Lions 91st season in franchise history}}\n{{Infobox NFL season\n| team            = Detroit Lions\n| logo            = Detroit Lions wordmark.svg\n| year            = 2020\n| record          = \n| division_place  = \n| coach           = [[Matt Patricia]]\n| general manager = [[Bob Quinn (American football)|Bob Quinn]]\n| owner           = [[Martha Firestone Ford]]\n| stadium         = [[Ford Field]]\n| playoffs        =\n| pro bowlers     =\n| uniform         = \n| shortnavlink    = Lions seasons\n}}\nThe [[2020 NFL season|2020 season]] will be the [[Detroit Lions]]' upcoming 91st in the [[National Football League]] and their third under [[List of Detroit Lions head coaches|head coach]] [[Matt Patricia]]. They will look to improve on their 3\u201312\u20131 record from the [[2019 Detroit Lions season|previous season]] and advance to the playoffs for the first time since [[2016 Detroit Lions season|2016]].\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Offseason==\n===Coaching changes===\n*On December 31, 2019, the Lions fired strength coach [[Harold Nash]], special-teams coordinator [[John Bonamego]], defensive backs coach [[Brian Stewart (American football)|Brian Stewart]], linebackers coach [[Al Golden]], tight ends coach Chris White and assistant strength coach Rodney Hill.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2019/12/31/detroit-lions-fire-strength-coach-special-teams-coordinator-other-assistants/2786312001/ |title=Detroit Lions fire strength coach, special-teams coordinator and 4 other assistant coaches |newspaper=Detroit Free Press |date=December 31, 2019 |accessdate=December 31, 2019}}</ref>\n*On January 2, 2020, defensive coordinator [[Paul Pasqualoni]] retired and offensive line coach [[Jeff Davidson]] took an \"indefinite leave\" from coaching.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/01/02/paul-pasqualoni-out-detroit-lions-defensive-coordinator/2798172001/ |title=Paul Pasqualoni out as Lions defensive coordinator, Jeff Davidson steps down as OL coach |newspaper=Detroit Free Press |date=January 2, 2020 |accessdate=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n*On January 13, the Lions hired [[Cory Undlin]] as defensive coordinator.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-hire-cory-undlin-as-defensive-coordinator |title=Lions hire Cory Undlin as defensive coordinator |work=Detroit Lions |date=January 13, 2020 |access-date=January 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Additions===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Date\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Player\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Position\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Previous team\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Contract\n!style=\"{{NFLPrimaryStyle|Detroit Lions|year=2019|border=2}}\"| Source\n|-\n| February 3\n| [[Joshua Garnett]]\n| [[Guard (gridiron football)|Guard]]\n| [[San Francisco 49ers]]\n| 1 year / $1.3 million \n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001101051/article/lions-sign-former-firstround-guard-joshua-garnett |title=Lions sign former first-round guard Joshua Garnett |website=NFL.com |first=Jeremy |last=Bergman |date=February 3, 2020 |accessdate=February 3, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"| March 16\n| [[Halapoulivaati Vaitai]] \n| [[Tackle (gridiron football position)|Tackle]]\n| [[Philadelphia Eagles]]\n| 5 years / $45 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/03/18/contract-breakdown-detroit-lions-lineman-halapoulivaati-vaitai/2863110001/