anta Falcons]]\n| 2 years / $21 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001106916/article/lions-ink-desmond-trufant-to-twoyear-21m-deal |title=Lions ink Desmond Trufant to two-year, $21M deal |website=NFL.com |first=Jelani |last=Scott |date=March 18, 2020 |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 19\n| [[Jayron Kearse]]\n| [[Safety (gridiron football position)|Safety]]\n| [[Minnesota Vikings]]\n| 1 year / $2 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.freep.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/03/19/jayron-kearse-detroit-lions/2872570001/ |title=Detroit Lions land more help for secondary, add ex-Minnesota Vikings S Jayron Kearse |newspaper=Detroit Free Press |first=Dave |last=Birkett |date=March 19, 2020 |accessdate=March 19, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 20\n| [[Tony McRae (American football)|Tony McRae]]\n| [[Cornerback]]\n| [[Cincinnati Bengals]]\n| 1 year / $1.5 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitnews.com/story/sports/nfl/lions/2020/03/20/lions-arent-done-yet-reach-agreement-cb-tony-mcrae/2887043001/ |title=Lions aren't done yet, reach agreement with CB Tony McRae |newspaper=The Detroit News |first=Justin |last=Rogers |date=March 20, 2020 |accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| March 27\n| [[Reggie Ragland]]\n| [[Linebacker]]\n| [[Kansas City Chiefs]]\n| 1 year / $1.0475 million\n| rowspan=\"2\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.detroitlions.com/news/lions-agree-to-terms-with-free-agent-lbs-elijah-lee-reggie-ragland |title=Lions agree to terms with free agent LBs Elijah Lee & Reggie Ragland |work=Detroit Lions |date=March 27, 2020 |accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Elijah Lee]]\n| [[Linebacker]]\n| [[San Francisco 49ers]] \n| 1 year / $835,000\n|-\n| March 29\n| [[Geronimo Allison]]\n| [[Wide receiver]]\n| [[Green Bay Packers]]\n| 1 year / $1.0475 million\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001107812/article/lions-sign-former-packers-wideout-geronimo-allison |title=Roundup: L