{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belize", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Belize}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belize\n| map1 = \n| legend1 = \n| map2 = \n| legend2 =  \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Belize]]\n| first_case = [[San Pedro Town]]\n| arrival_date = 19 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=19|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases = 5\n| deaths = 2<ref>{{cite web |title=Belize records first Covid-19 death |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/05/belize-records-first-covid-19-death/ |publisher=Breaking Belize News |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 18<ref>{{cite news|title=Tracking the detection and history of COVID-19 cases in Belize|url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/13/tracking-the-detection-and-history-of-covid-19-cases-in-belize/|website=Breaking Belize News|access-date=14 April 2020}}</ref> (2020-04-13)\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili = \n| website = \n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Belize]] in March 2020.\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n===March 2020===\nThe country's first case was announced on 23 March, a Belizean woman who returned to [[San Pedro Town]] from [[Los Angeles, California]].<ref name=\"gov-1st-case\">{{cite web|url=http://health.gov.bz/www/component/content/article/177-general-health/1028-ministry-of-health-announces-first-case-of-covid-19|title=Ministry of Health Announces First Case of COVID-19|date=23 March 2020|work=Ministry of Health (Belize)|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/23/belize-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-cuban-doctors-arriving-to-help/|title=Belize confirms first case of coronavirus, Cuban doctors arriving to help|website=Breaking Belize News|date=23 March 2020|accessdate=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=First Covid-19 patient in Belize is San Pedro resident |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/23/first-covid-19-patient-in-belize-is-san-pedro-resident/ |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News |date=23 March 2020}}</ref> The second case was announced on 25 March. They had immediate contact with the first case.<ref>{{Cite news|last=BBN Staff|first=|url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/25/ministry-of-health-confirms-2nd-covid-19-positive-case-awaiting-results-of-more-tests/|title=Ministry of Health confirms 2nd covid-19 positive case; awaiting results of more tests|date=25 March 2020|work=Breaking Belize News|access-date=30 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe third case in Belize was announced on 29 March from a traveler returning to [[Belize City]] from [[New York City]].<ref name=\"fifth\">{{Cite news|last=BBN Staff|first=|url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/29/minister-of-health-confirms-third-covid-19-case-is-in-belize-city-and-imported-from-new-york/|title=Minister of Health confirms third Covid-19 case is in Belize City and imported from New York|date=29 March 2020|work=Breaking Belize News|access-date=30 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\n\nThe 5th confirmed case of coronavirus was confirmed in a Belizean student who returned from [[Florida]] in the United States. He is currently in self-isolation at a quarantine facility and has no symptoms.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fifth Case of COVID-19 Confirmed in Belize |url=https://www.ambergristoday.com/news/2020/04/05/fifth-case-of-covid-19-confirmed-in-belize |website=Ambergris Today |accessdate=6 April 2020 |language=en |date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Prevention measures==\nIn the light of the recent event, Prime Minister [[Dean Barrow]] has declared State of Emergency for San Pedro. Residents of [[Ambergris Caye]] are being placed under mandatory quarantine. Onl\u0443 \u0435ss\u0435nti\u0430l w\u043erk\u0435rs will be \u0430ll\u043ew\u0435d to tr\u0430v\u0435rs\u0435 the str\u0435\u0435ts. \"Un\u0430uth\u043eriz\u0435d v\u0435ss\u0435ls will be b\u0430nn\u0435d fr\u043em l\u0435\u0430ving \u043er \u0430rriving on the isl\u0430nd,\u201d \u0430 \u0455t\u0430t\u0435m\u0435nt fr\u043em the G\u043ev\u0435rnm\u0435nt s\u0430id. At this time the Ministry of Health is tracing everyone that may have been in contact with the Belizean woman who tested positive for the Covid-19.<ref>{{Cite web |title=State of Emergency declared for San Pedro; residents placed under mandatory quarantine|url= https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/23/state-of-emergency-declared-for-san-pedro-residents-placed-under-mandatory-quarantine/|website=Breaking Belize News|date=23 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nPrime Minister [[Dean Barrow]] had also closed schools on March 20 and it will resume on April 20th pending any changes in the situation. He has banned public gathering of more than 25 people and he has closed all borders. All flights have been grounded effective March 23. Only cargo would be able to cross the borders and docked by sea. Belizeans are still allowed to return to Belize but residents will not be allow to leave the country unless it is an emergency.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/22/government-issues-reminder-of-border-closures/|title=Government issues reminder of border closures|website=Breaking Belize News|date=23 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/22/immigration-officials-belizeans-will-be-allowed-to-come-home/|title=Immigration officials: 'Belizeans will be allowed to come home'|website=Breaking Belize News|date=23 March 2020|access-date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe Minister of health asks that anyone having flu-like symptoms stay home, self-isolate, and call the hotline at 0-800-MOH-CARE for further guidance.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn March 30, a state of emergency was announced across the country, as well as a curfew from 8p.m. to 5a.m.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/30/prime-minister-dean-barrow-announces-countrywide-state-of-emergency/|title=Prime Minister Dean Barrow announces countrywide state of emergency|date=30 March 2020|work=Breaking Belize News|access-date=2 April 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn early April, the government announced that borders would be closed to all travellers, including Belizean nationals except for emergency situations.<ref>{{cite news |title=Belize is now on war footing; PM Barrow announces closure of borders to national |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/03/belize-is-now-on-war-footing-pm-barrow-announces-closure-of-borders-to-national/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=3 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=All borders closed to the entry of Belizean nationals |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/05/all-borders-closed-to-the-entry-of-belizean-nationals/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=5 April 2020}}</ref> Other travel restrictions, including quarantines, had already been implemented in March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Government issues reminder of border closures |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/03/22/government-issues-reminder-of-border-closures/ |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=Breaking Belize News-The Leading Online News Source of Belize |date=22 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe government declared an emergency Declaration of a countrywide state curfew. The curfew was set from April 1 to April 30th. The curfew is from 8pm to 5am.\n\n==See also==\n{{Div col}}\n*[[Caribbean Public Health Agency]]\n*[[2020 in Central America]]\n*[[History of smallpox in Mexico]]\n*[[HIV/AIDS in Latin America]]\n*[[2013\u20132014 chikungunya outbreak]]\n*[[2009 swine flu pandemic]]\n*[[2019\u20132020 dengue fever epidemic]]\n*[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in North America]]\n{{End div col}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 in Belize|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Belize]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Central America|Belize]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Belize]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Belize}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belize\n| map1 = \n| legend1 = \n| map2 = \n| legend2 =  \n| map3 = \n| legend3 = \n| disease = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location = [[Belize]]\n| first_case = [[San Pedro Town]]\n| arrival_date = 19 March 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=3|day1=19|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin = [[Wuhan]], [[China]]\n| recovery_cases = 5\n| deaths = 2<ref>{{cite web |title=Belize records first Covid-19 death |url=https://www.breakingbelizenews.com/2020/04/05/belize-records-first-covid-19-death/ |publisher=Breaking Belize News |accessdate=6 April 2020 |date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 18<ref>{{cite news|titl